This paper discusses the use of machine learning and artificial intelligence in creating social bots, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP) and computational linguistics (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper also discusses the potential for coordinated campaigns of deception and influence, which could fall under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), social and information networks (cs.SI), cybersecurity (cs.CY), and systems and control (cs.SD).
